|TUN|1992 Summer|14}}\n* {{flagIOC|TUR|1992 Summer|47}}\n* {{flagIOC|UGA|1992 Summer|8}}\n* {{flagIOC|EUN|1992 Summer|475}}\n* {{flagIOC|UAE|1992 Summer|14}}\n* {{flagIOC|USA|1992 Summer|545}}\n* {{flagIOC|URU|1992 Summer|23}}\n* {{flagIOC|VAN|1992 Summer|6}}\n* {{flagIOC|VEN|1992 Summer|37}}\n* {{flagIOC|VIE|1992 Summer|7}}\n* {{flagIOC|ISV|1992 Summer|24}}\n* {{flagIOC|SAM|1992 Summer|5}}\n* {{flagIOC|YEM|1992 Summer|13}}\n* {{flagIOC|ZAI|1992 Summer|17}}\n* {{flagIOC|ZAM|1992 Summer|9}}\n* {{flagIOC|ZIM|1992 Summer|19}}\n{{div col end}}\n|}\n\n* {{flagIOC|BRU}} participated in the Opening Ceremony, but its delegation consisted of only one official. This also occurred in the [[1988 Summer Olympics|1988 Games]]<ref name=\"Olympics Official Report\">{{cite book |title=1992 Olympics Official Report. Part IV |url=http://la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1992/1992s4p4.pdf |format=PDF |accessdate=24 October 2012|quote=List of participants by NOC's and sport. }}</ref><ref>{{YouTube|3Dfntr38rwc|Barcelona 1992 Opening Ceremony Parade of Nations 2/8}}</ref>\n* {{Flagicon|AFG|1987}} [[Afghanistan at the Olympics|Afghanistan]] didn't send their athletes to compete, but the country took part in the Parade of Nations.<ref>{{YouTube|-Rtfp1oCkGk|Barcelona 1992 Opening Ceremony Parade of Nations 1/8}}</ref>\n* {{flagIOC|LBR}}<ref>{{YouTube|7mSyyqxSLEA|Barcelona 1992 Opening Ceremony Parade of Nations 4/8}}</ref> and {{flagIOC|SOM}}<ref>{{YouTube|uddDBgdFF04|Barcelona 1992 Opening Ceremony Parade of Nations 6/8}}</ref> also participated in the Opening Ceremony, but its accredited athletes (five and two, respectively) did not enter to compete.<ref name=\"Olympics Official Report\" />\n\n== Medal count ==\n{{Main|1992 Summer Olympics medal table}}\nThe following table reflects the top ten nations in terms of total medals won at the 1992 Games (the host nation is highlighted).\n{{Medals table\n | caption        = \n | host           = \n | show_limit     = \n | remaining_text = 