ctoria (Australia)|Victoria]], [[Australia]]. It has operated between the heads of [[Port Phillip|Port Phillip Bay]] between the towns of [[Queenscliff, Victoria|Queenscliff]] and [[Sorrento, Victoria|Sorrento]] since December 1993.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dpc.vic.gov.au/domino/Web_Notes/pressrel.nsf/0cc988f35cba63df4a25620d002c68f3/ce757a23163f570f4a2561f100330b39!OpenDocument&Click= |work=Media Release |publisher=Office of the Premier |title=Premier Launches New Bay Ferry Service |date=22 December 1993 |accessdate=26 July 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930223526/http://www.dpc.vic.gov.au/domino/Web_Notes/pressrel.nsf/0cc988f35cba63df4a25620d002c68f3/ce757a23163f570f4a2561f100330b39%21OpenDocument%26Click%3D |archivedate=30 September 2007 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The ferry replaced the earlier ''[[Peninsula Princess (Australia)|Peninsula Princess]]'' used on the route, and can carry approximately 80 vehicles and 700 passengers.<ref name=\"searoad\"/> During the 2011 off season the ferry underwent a $2 Million refit.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.intown.com.au/locals/queenscliff/queenscliff-sorrento-ferry.htm |title=Queenscliff Sorrento Ferry |accessdate=30 September 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Loading and unloading==\nThe MV ''Queenscliff'' is fitted with ramps at the bow and stern of the ship to allow vehicles to roll on at the start of the voyage and roll off at the end of the voyage. This results in a fast turnaround time, with all vehicles and passengers embarking and disembarking in approximately 15 to 20 minutes. The loading facilities are also used by the [[MV Sorrento (2001)|MV ''Sorrento'']], the earlier ''Peninsula Princess'' used a different ramp at Queenscliff.\n\nAt Queenscliff, the ship docks bow into the terminal. The bow of the ship consists of two sections; one section raises whilst the other lowers forming a ramp that allows vehicles to drive off. Once all vehicles and foot passengers have disembarked the ship, vehicles travelling to Sorrento then board and face the stern of the ship for the voyage. At Sorrento, the ship docks stern into the terminal. A ramp at the stern of the ship lowers allowing vehicles to drive off. Once all vehicles and foot passengers have disembarked, vehicles travelling to Queenscliff then board and face the bow of the ship for the voyage.\n\nFoot passengers embark and disembark the ship, via the same ramps that vehicles do, under the direction of the ship's crew in between the embarkation and disembarkation of vehicles.\n\n==Gallery==\n{{multiple image\n| footer    = \n| align     = left\n| image1    = The Searoad Queenscliff-Sorrento Ferry 'Queenscliff', rear view leaving Queenscliff, jjron, 06.07.2010.jpg\n| width1    = {{#expr: (200 * 1600 / 1067) round 0}}\n| alt1      = Rear view of the ferry\n| caption1  = Rear view of the ferry\n| image2    = The Searoad Queenscliff-Sorrento Ferry 'MV Queenscliff' Interior, jjron, 05.07.2010.jpg\n| width2    = {{#expr: (200 * 1600 / 1067) round 0}}\n| alt2      = Pre refit interior view of the ferry\n| caption2  = Pre refit interior view of the ferry\n}}\n{{-}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[MV Sorrento (2001)|MV ''Sorrento'']]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|IMO 9074171}}\n*[http://www.searoad.com.au Peninsula Searoad Ferry]\n\n{{Australianferries}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Queenscliff}}\n[[Category:Ferries of Victoria (Australia)]]\n[[Category:Transport in Geelong]]\n[[Category:Transport in Victoria (Australia)]]\n[[Category:1992 ships]]\n[[Category:Port Phillip]]\n", "name_user": "Davey2010", "label": "safe", "comment": "Cleaned up usingAutoEd", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MV_Queenscliff_(1992)"}
